race.description: Become A Member & Save Maiden Handicap
race.comment: YALDA NIGHT (1) was trending the right way before a disappointing performance when out to 1800m as Ascot last time out. The winner there was very impressive however, with the margin looking worse than YALDA NIGHT's run really was. Easier here and can take closer order from an inside alley. Looks the one to beat. ROSENTREA (2) came back to a similar race last start and only just missed out on victory, beaten in a photo over 1500m. Back out in trip looks ideal for her now and she can be prominent from the inside alley. 2kg claim comes in handy and she's the main danger. SAUCISSON (8) rattled home last start over 1500m and looks suited by the rise in trip today. Can improve on that performance out in trip and he's expected to make his presence felt. IFFUBLUSH (11) has trialled since her latest effort and coming back in trip may hold the key. OPAL NERO (5) is not out of this.
